// The sync guarantee for target profiles: `wl_only` exists only in tgfx's wayland variant (the linux
// target). Under the windows target tgfx is backed by dx12, so the call is unresolved — and the
// COMPILER and the ANALYZER must agree. ARCHE_TARGET (read by both front-ends) overrides the manifest's
// `target = "linux"`, also exercising env-overrides-manifest precedence.
//
// Compiler: rejects under windows, accepts under linux. (`!` — POSIX shell negation — not the LLVM
// `not` utility, which isn't installed on the CI runner.)
// RUN: ! env ARCHE_TARGET=windows %arche check %s
// RUN: env ARCHE_TARGET=linux %arche check %s
//
// Analyzer: reports the SAME error under windows, and is clean under linux.
// RUN: env ARCHE_TARGET=windows %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | grep "has no member 'wl_only'"
// RUN: ! env ARCHE_TARGET=linux %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | grep "has no member"
#import { tgfx }
main :: proc() {
  tgfx.wl_only();
}
